<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-19"><hi rend="italic">November 19,
                                    1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Missionaries at Bitlis telegraph for escort for all to Van, and those at
                            Harpoot wish to come here. Telegraphic orders to furnish safe escort
                            demanded and sent for all. If you can spare another, send a vessel to
                            Smyrna, to go thence wherever needed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>